The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks for artificial intelligence applications, specifically in the field of computer vision. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on transfer learning and data augmentation techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning and deep learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also discusses the computational cost of implementing these techniques, which suggests that it may belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a method for improving the efficiency of deep learning models, which may also place it in the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category.
